history.content:
Regardless of whether or not it is a pre-req, I do not recommend enrolling in EE 120 without EE 16B.
If you took EE 16A last year (Fall 2015) and "got" the DFT stuff that was shoe-horned into the end, then you would probbaly be fine, with some front-loaded "catch up" work, if you *really* wanted to jump right into 120). My understanding is that the current iteration of 16A is not going to cover DFT at all (though I may be wrong on that).

But 120 definitely feels like more of a follow-up to 16B than A. In addition to DFT, you are expected to know transfer functions/Bode analysis and a few other things that are covered in 16B but not A.

Another response: I took 120 at the same time with 16B and I got away fine. I don't necessarily think it's needed but it would be better if you have a basic understanding of Fourier Transform.
